<br>
I have spent 85 AA as a level 60 archmage, and I can tell you the qualitative difference of being an archmage is tremendous. The combinition of spells, resists, and other level related effects beats anything AA offers a mage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So you're saying level 60 = mana free soloing?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You would spend your time better by getting your epic instead of wasting exp on AA right now <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
How much levelling will I be able to do while trying to get Epic?  I am blending AA and levelling, because I don't want to get behind on either.  Soloing with no downtime is very very important to me, and doing it without outside assistance even more so.  If I want to spend an hour or two playing the game, then soloing is generally the way to go.  IR affords me the power to solo pretty much where I want, when I want, with no downtime, and no need for clarity buffs.  Level 60 all by itself can't do that for me.<br>
<br>
