<br>
I don't think I'll gain big advantages if I level higher then 61.  We do epic stuff all the time.  Quite a lot of this will become light blue and green if I was level 65.  Moving through chardok, killing mobs in skyfire for shards, clearing out City of Mist, etc.  I want to actually get exp on our raids if I can.<br>
<br>
Level 61 gave me one of the major nuke increases I want.  It's damn fun to land 3k+ crits with FoT.  I enjoy playing immensely right now.  I want to polish off the AA I feel are worth getting while my guild still does lots of 45-50 level mobs.  Then if they someday move on to mainly 51-65 mobs I will be content being level 65 and I'll move up then.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I see no reason to ding 62 if I have none of my 61+ spells besides FoT.  If I actually had those spells banked, I'll consider it.<br>
<br>
I like soloing, I like grouping. I DON'T WANT MY OPTIONS TAKEN AWAY!  Seems to me lvl 65 means nearly the end of soloing.  I really really really hope Sony changes exp levels on mobs.  If they do, I'll go ahead and level.  If they don't I'm in no rush to be level 65. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Eandori Raintree Arch Mage<br>
