Half of our pets is the Burnout buff.  At level 46, Burnout II is our best option, which is only 35% haste.  Still...I would have loved to get my hands on my epic at 46!<br>
<br>
Secondly, my thoughts on Fungus Grove.  Shrooms can be tough mobs if done unproperly.  They slow, which is disease based, and that REALLY kills the damage output of our pets.  However, shrooms have really low AC and moderately low resists.  My Monster Summoning II pet does 30-40dps consistant against these shrooms as long as it's not slowed.  Other than that, they have a lot of HP.  I think they're somewhere around 8800hp.<br>
<br>
Also, I think you need to be level 60 to single pull the shrooms, but don't quote me on that one.  I two-box a level 60 shaman when I play a lot, but lately it's just a hassle.  I can solo Echo Caverns with 100% ease and get faster exp than trudging it in FG against shrooms.  Then again, I'm only level 50 right now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30>Magician Skills</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
